14. "Ethereum’s narrative always changes"
 
ICOs, DeFi, NFTs - all of these are emergent apps on Ethereum
 
Social media, email, video streaming - all of these were emergent apps on the internet
 
But the internet was just a communication protocol, always was. 
 
Same thing.

13. "ETH is just a tech stock"
 
Partially true, but it's more bullish than it seems.
 
$ETH is trading at a PE of ~32 (on par with $AAPL & $GOOG)
 
What's neglected is the monetary premium from $ETH as collateral in DeFi & staking

Don't sleep on the premium 😴

12. “Scalability reduces the burn”
 
Yes, tx fees will drop on an individual basis but it balances out as Ethereum can process more txs
 
We see this as it's scaled by ~50x since genesis via gas limit increases & smart contract gas optimizations
 
Have we seen a decrease in fees? https://t.co/71i7eLy4SB

11. "ETH is a security"

In the 200+ jurisdictions in the world, not one has deemed ETH a security.
 
What about the U.S?
 
1⃣ SEC has given informal guidance pre-Gary stating not a security
2⃣ CFTC stated it's a commodity
3⃣ Past the 7 yr statute of limitations
 
@GaryGensler 😘

10. "Higher ETH price, the higher the gas fees"
 
This is a misconception.
 
The ETH/USD market is completely independent from the gas market.
 
Therefore, it's entirely possible to have $1M $ETH and $0.01 gas fees

9. "Deflation is bad"
 
This comes from traditional economist thinking.
 
But it really depends on the type of money. There are two types:
 
1⃣Debt money (fiat) = inflation good
2⃣Collateral money (gold) = deflation good
 
Both $ETH and $BTC optimize for collateral money.

8. "PoS is just a rich get richer scheme"
 
Sort of???
 
Everyone gets the same APR.
 
Meaning, the rich stay equally as rich and the poor stay equally as poor
 
This is unlike PoW which requires millions of $$$ to reach economies of scale & have a competitive miner

PoS > PoW

7. "ETH is a plutocracy"
 
This is false.
 
Neither Ethereum validators or $ETH holders have on-chain governance rights.
 
All macro governance decisions happen on the social layer
 
The same is true for Bitcoin.

6. "ETH supply is unpredictable"
 
True - ETH's monetary policy has changed via the social layer, not programmatically.
 
But not anymore.
 
ETH issuance becomes programmatic based on market dynamics after the merge.
 
You can model it with 2 variables: Cost of money & fees https://t.co/HBiqqZPTJz

5. "ETH has an infinite supply"
 
This was partially true pre-EIP 1559.
 
But now the burn counterbalances ETH issuance. Why?
 
🔥 Burn is linear
💸 Issuance is sub-linear
 
This simple model guarantees a supply equilibrium in the future. https://t.co/yuguP99sQN

4. "Ethereum can’t be both money & a settlement layer"
 
It's actually the opposite.
 
In order to have a settlement layer for the world's economic activity, you need trillions of economic security.
 
This is only possible with a native money worth trillions💰

3. "Ethereum is trying to be everything at once"
 
This is like saying the internet is trying to do everything. 
 
The internet is a digital communication layer.
 
Ethereum is a settlement layer for digital value.
 
Both have a singular goal.

2. "Ethereum will never ship"
 
From the genesis block, to EIP 1559, to the Merge, people think Ethereum will never ship.
 
This has been proven wrong time and time again.

15. Ultra Sound Money is cringe
 
Can't dispute this.
 
Cringiness is subjective @udiWertheimer 
 
But people like the meme sooo 🤷‍♂️

14. "Ethereum’s narrative always changes"
 
ICOs, DeFi, NFTs - all of these are emergent apps on Ethereum
 
Social media, email, video streaming - all of these were emergent apps on the internet
 
But the internet was just a communication protocol, always was. 
 
Same thing.

13. "ETH is just a tech stock"
 
Partially true, but it's more bullish than it seems.
 
$ETH is trading at a PE of ~32 (on par with $AAPL & $GOOG)
 
What's neglected is the monetary premium from $ETH as collateral in DeFi & staking

Don't sleep on the premium 😴

12. “Scalability reduces the burn”
 
Yes, tx fees will drop on an individual basis but it balances out as Ethereum can process more txs
 
We see this as it's scaled by ~50x since genesis via gas limit increases & smart contract gas optimizations
 
Have we seen a decrease in fees? https://t.co/71i7eLy4SB

11. "ETH is a security"

In the 200+ jurisdictions in the world, not one has deemed ETH a security.
 
What about the U.S?
 
1⃣ SEC has given informal guidance pre-Gary stating not a security
2⃣ CFTC stated it's a commodity
3⃣ Past the 7 yr statute of limitations
 
@GaryGensler 😘

10. "Higher ETH price, the higher the gas fees"
 
This is a misconception.
 
The ETH/USD market is completely independent from the gas market.
 
Therefore, it's entirely possible to have $1M $ETH and $0.01 gas fees

9. "Deflation is bad"
 
This comes from traditional economist thinking.
 
But it really depends on the type of money. There are two types:
 
1⃣Debt money (fiat) = inflation good
2⃣Collateral money (gold) = deflation good
 
Both $ETH and $BTC optimize for collateral money.

8. "PoS is just a rich get richer scheme"
 
Sort of???
 
Everyone gets the same APR.
 
Meaning, the rich stay equally as rich and the poor stay equally as poor
 
This is unlike PoW which requires millions of $$$ to reach economies of scale & have a competitive miner

PoS > PoW

7. "ETH is a plutocracy"
 
This is false.
 
Neither Ethereum validators or $ETH holders have on-chain governance rights.
 
All macro governance decisions happen on the social layer
 
The same is true for Bitcoin.

6. "ETH supply is unpredictable"
 
True - ETH's monetary policy has changed via the social layer, not programmatically.
 
But not anymore.
 
ETH issuance becomes programmatic based on market dynamics after the merge.
 
You can model it with 2 variables: Cost of money & fees https://t.co/HBiqqZPTJz

5. "ETH has an infinite supply"
 
This was partially true pre-EIP 1559.
 
But now the burn counterbalances ETH issuance. Why?
 
🔥 Burn is linear
💸 Issuance is sub-linear
 
This simple model guarantees a supply equilibrium in the future. https://t.co/yuguP99sQN

4. "Ethereum can’t be both money & a settlement layer"
 
It's actually the opposite.
 
In order to have a settlement layer for the world's economic activity, you need trillions of economic security.
 
This is only possible with a native money worth trillions💰

3. "Ethereum is trying to be everything at once"
 
This is like saying the internet is trying to do everything. 
 
The internet is a digital communication layer.
 
Ethereum is a settlement layer for digital value.
 
Both have a singular goal.

2. "Ethereum will never ship"
 
From the genesis block, to EIP 1559, to the Merge, people think Ethereum will never ship.
 
This has been proven wrong time and time again.
 
Today is another example.
